{
  "texts": [
    "Crucially, human presencing is not a pure reconstruction of past events and could never be investigated or studied in pure isolation.",
    "Building on Bartlett's (1932) insights that remembering is activity, Sutton and Williamson (2014) argue that embodied remembering is context-sensitive.",
    "Through the recursive use of her body, Paula actively scaffolded her immediate physical environment to bring forth the spatial and temporal dimensions of her cognitive ecology.",
    "Human presencing also occurred through recursive wholebody engagement, as Paula continually gestured to her left (§ 6.1).",
    "This scaffolding of her physical environment (i.e., the interview room) allowed her to re-evoke and ascribe significance to her past experiences from her engagement in the classroom."
  ]
}